  "coverStory": {
    "title": {
      "zh": "宇宙的隱形繩結：從夸克到質子的自旋密碼",
      "en": "The Spin of the Vacuum: Unraveling Quark Confinement Through Hyperon Pairs"
    },
    "summary": {
      "zh": "【結果】短距離（ΔR < 0.5）的ΛΛ̄對顯示0.181的自旋相關性（4.4倍標準差），遠高於背景預期。此結果與SU(6)夸克模型預測的1/3（33.3%）相符，證明夸克自旋在強子化中幾乎未被破壞。而當粒子距離增大，相關性急劇下降，暗示量子退相干效應的存在。這不僅驗證了QCD真空中的夸克-condensate模型，更為量子資訊科學與強相互作用的交叉研究開拓新視野，讓物理學家首次在實驗室中見證「量子糾纏」如何影響物質世界的形成。",
      "en": "**Results:** Short-range ΛΛ̄ pairs showed a spin correlation of 0.181 ± 0.035 (stat) ± 0.022 (sys), a 4.4σ deviation from zero. This value aligns with theoretical predictions for spin-triplet states, indicating that quark spins remain largely coherent during hadronization. As pairs separated, correlation rapidly decayed, suggesting quantum decoherence from strong interactions. This discovery validates the SU(6) quark model's prediction that strange quarks dominate Λ hyperon spin, while also providing a new experimental probe for quantum information studies in high-energy physics."
    },
